    4954         320 : static void check_dialect_and_language_modes(void)
    4955             : /*
    4956             : Check for consistent specification of dialects and language modes.  Dialect
    4957             : inconsistencies are not allowed (and have been diagnosed previously).
    4958             : Language modes that are specified are required to be consistent with the
    4959             : operative dialect.
    4960             : 
    4961             : Here is a summary of the dialects and modes, along with the associated
    4962             : command line switches.
    4963             : 
    4964             :     dialect/mode        associated global variable       option
    4965             :     ============        ==========================       ======
    4966             :   C                                                      --c, -m
    4967             :     pcc mode            C_dialect == C_dialect_pcc       --old_c, -K
    4968             :     "ANSI" [= not pcc]  C_dialect == C_dialect_ANSI      (default)
    4969             :       SVR4 mode         SVR4_C_mode                      --svr4
    4970             :       microsoft mode    ms_extensions, ms_compat, microsoft_mode
    4971             :                                                          --microsoft
    4972             :         MS compatibility ms_extensions, ms_compat        --ms_compatibility
    4973             :         MS extensions   ms_extensions                    --ms_extensions
    4974             :         bugs mode       microsoft_bugs                   --microsoft_bugs
    4975             :         16-bit mode     il_header.near_and_far_allowed   --microsoft_16
    4976             :       C99               std_version >= 199901            --c99
    4977             :       C11               std_version >= 201112            --c11
    4978             :         strict          strict_ansi_mode                 -A, -a, etc.
    4979             :       "normal"            
    4980             :         strict          strict_ansi_mode                 -A, -a, etc.
    4981             :       GNU C             gcc_mode                         --gcc
    4982             :       clang C           gcc_mode && clang_mode           --c --clang
    4983             : 
    4984             :   C++                   C_dialect == C_dialect_cplusplus --c++, -p
    4985             :     cfront mode
    4986             :       2.1 mode          cfront_2_1_mode                  --cfront_2.1
    4987             :       3.0 mode          cfront_3_0_mode                  --cfront_3.0
    4988             :     microsoft mode      ms_extensions, ms_compat, microsoft_mode
    4989             :                                                          --microsoft
    4990             :       MS compatibility  ms_extensions, ms_compat         --ms_compatibility
    4991             :       MS extensions     ms_extensions                    --ms_extensions
    4992             :       bugs mode         microsoft_bugs                   --microsoft_bugs
    4993             :       16-bit mode       il_header.near_and_far_allowed   --microsoft_16
    4994             :     sun mode            sun_mode                         --sun
    4995             :     GNU C++             gpp_mode                         --g++
    4996             :     clang C++           gpp_mode && clang_mode           --clang
    4997             :     C++03               std_version >= 199711            --c++03
    4998             :     C++11               std_version >= 201103            --c++11
    4999             :     C++14               std_version >= 201402            --c++14
    5000             :     C++17               std_version >= 201701 (?)        --c++17
    5001             :     "normal"
    5002             :       strict            strict_ansi_mode                 -A, -a, etc.
    5003             : 
    5004             : The major C dialect (K&R, ANSI, or C++) is determined by a command line option
    5005             : (if any) that selects a major dialect, either implicitly (e.g., --g++ or
    5006             : --embedded_c) or explicitly (e.g., --c++ or --c).  The specification of two or
    5007             : more command line options that either implicitly or explicitly set the major
    5008             : dialect to different values is an error.  No major dialect is implicitly
    5009             : specified with --microsoft et al. or --strict et al.  --sun cannot be combined
    5010             : with command-line options to select a C mode, but otherwise it implies C++ mode
    5011             : (even in the somewhat unusual event that the front end were modified to compile
    5012             : C code by default).
    5013             : 
    5014             : Beginning with Visual Studio 2015 Update 3 (aka, microsoft_version 1903
    5015             : internally), the command-line options --ms_c++14 and --ms_c++latest have been
    5016             : introduced to emulate the corresponding /std:c++14 and /std:c++latest
    5017             : command-line options.  Strictly speaking these are not treated as "modes";
    5018             : rather those command-line options turn on individual features (via global
    5019             : variables) to enable the same set of features that would be available in
    5020             : the specified version of Visual Studio.  Note that --c++14 (i.e., the ISO set
    5021             : of C++14 features) is not guaranteed to be the same as --ms_c++14 (i.e.,
    5022             : Microsoft's implemented set) though these may converge in the future.
    5023             : 
    5024             : Microsoft emulation has been split into three "tiers": --ms_extensions
    5025             : emulates clang's -fms-extensions mode, --ms_compatibility emulates clang's
    5026             : -fms-compatibility mode, and --microsoft enables full Microsoft compatibility.
    5027             : Only the last of these modes qualifies as a "major dialect", thereby allowing
    5028             : --ms_extensions, and/or --ms_compatibility to be specified with other major
    5029             : dialects (e.g., --clang).
    5030             : 
    5031             : A mode for a newer standard (like C99 or C++11) is in some ways considered
    5032             : both a dialect and a mode.  For example, with --c99 C_dialect is still
    5033             : C_dialect_ANSI, but it can also be used in conjunction with Microsoft mode.
    5034             : Likewise for --c++11 which implicitly sets the dialect to C_dialect_cplusplus
    5035             : and also sets std_version.
    5036             : 
    5037             : clang mode is a variant of GNU mode.  Specifying --clang or --clang_version
    5038             : will implicitly set gcc_mode or gpp_mode.
    5039             : 
    5040             : Although not recommended, some conflicting language modes can be specified on
    5041             : the command line with the last option being effective (e.g., --c89 --c99
    5042             : results in C99 mode).
    5043             : 
    5044             : Note that the fact that K&R C is its own major dialect, rather than being a
    5045             : minor dialect under C mode, is a historical accident of the order of
    5046             : development of this front end, and is inconsistent and strange.
